olive oil
1 capsicum
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 packet beef mince
½ packet tomato paste
1 packet garlic paste
1 tsp honey
⅓ cup water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet roasted almonds
1 sachet Tunisian seasoning
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 leek

Boil a kettle of water. Roughly chop the capsicum.
Thinly slice the leek.

In a medium bowl, combine the couscous and
chicken-style stock powder. Add the boiling
water (see ingredients) and stir to combine.
Immediately cover with a plate and set aside for
5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.

While the couscous is cooking, heat a large frying
pan over a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook the capsicum and leek until slightly charred,
4-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

Return the frying pan to a high heat with a drizzle
of olive oil. Cook the beef mince, breaking it up
with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

Reduce the heat to medium. Add the tomato
paste (see ingredients), garlic paste and Tunisian
seasoning and cook until fragrant, 30 seconds.
Add the water and a drizzle of honey, then return
the veggies to the pan and cook, stirring to
combine, 1 minute. Stir through the baby spinach
leaves until wilted, 1 minute. Season to taste.

Divide the couscous between bowls. Top with
the Tunisian and honey-coated beef and veggies.
Garnish with the roasted almonds and serve with
the Greek-style yoghurt.